<h3 id="zyuAPj"><a href="https://www.curbed.com/2019/8/7/20756886/round-chunky-cozy-furniture-design-trends">The Rise of Round</a></h3>
<h4 id="M8nT9c">by Diana Budds</h4>
<p id="w08Cc8">“Perhaps they simply allow us to regress to a childlike state and remember life before we thought about politics and the trials of adulthood,” he says. “I think there’s something to be said for that—the feeling of sublime naivete. I really try to not overanalyze or intellectualize it.”</p>
