<h3 id="PmK184"><a href="https://www.curbed.com/2018/3/14/17115886/amazon-alexa-smart-home-google-automation-diy">Home smart home </a></h3>
<h4 id="FOFD3r">by Libby Copeland</h4>
<p id="jkYXu7">Like many smart home early adopters, Gomes has a <em>thing</em> he’s really into—a kind of technological cause—and his thing is lights. Finding the right light for one’s home is “super serious,” he says. “I truly believe in the future that more people will understand this.” So he worked with his interior designer to find a company that makes custom light bulbs, searched for just the right lamps and sconces, and then, with the help of his smart home integration service, tweaked and tweaked the lighting till it was the “perfect amber.” These days, Gomes is one of the leading brokers in Manhattan’s luxury real estate market, but the amber glow of his apartment reminds him of the days when he was a waiter at the French brasserie Balthazar, and the lighting was just right, and everyone looked that much more beautiful.</p>
<hr class="p-entry-hr" id="xMQh72">
<div class="c-wide-block">  <figure class="e-image">
  <span class="e-image__inner">
    
    <span class="e-image__image " data-original="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/10127757/GettyImages_583864874.jpg">
      
        <picture class="c-picture" data-cid="site/picture_element-1587428959_2152_52546" data-cdata='{"asset_id":10127757,"ratio":"*"}'>
  


